600 1130 846 (Should basic_string have a getline\(\) function?) 846 SB
300 1179 145 (Section:) 145 SB
600 1179 640 (21.1.1.4.5 \(new\) [lib.string::getline]) 640 SB
300 1228 125 (Status:) 125 SB
600 1228 118 (closed) 118 SB
300 1277 228 (Description:) 228 SB
600 1326 1436 (As identified by Beman Dawes in lib-3367, the 20 September 1994 draft of the) 1436 SB
600 1375 1464 (WP does not include getline\(\) .  It was part of the 27 May 1994 draft of the WP.) 1464 SB
600 1424 1458 (Beman suggested that getline\(\) be reinstated with the semantics as specified in) 1458 SB
600 1473 380 (the earlier WP draft.) 380 SB
600 1571 903 (In lib-3408, Nathan Myers responded as follows:) 903 SB
600 1620 1458 (\223I\222m quite concerned about the semantics implied in the string traits.  There, it) 1458 SB
600 1669 1479 (seems to be assumed that the end-of-line character is the same for all encodings) 1479 SB
600 1718 1467 (of a character type.  But, of course, even in ASCII we see an amazing variety of) 1467 SB
600 1767 1443 (line-end conventions.  Unicode is worse, with all the ASCII control characters) 1443 SB
600 1816 852 (and \(as I recall\) two more line-end characters.) 852 SB
600 1914 1492 (\223I fear that we cannot provide internationalized getline semantics with the same) 1492 SB
600 1963 1393 (interface that we have had.  I can imagine a getline\(\) which takes the user\222s) 1393 SB
600 2012 1380 (choice of line ending, but I can imagine you may want any of the available) 1380 SB
600 2061 1341 (choices to end a line.  The locale object\222s ctype facet does not provide an) 1341 SB
600 2110 1321 (\221is_eol\(\)\222 member, and POSIX does not provide the underlying support) 1321 SB
600 2159 703 (necessary to implement it in any case.) 703 SB
600 2257 1362 (\223It seems clear to me that the getline operation depends on the character-) 1362 SB
600 2306 1463 (encoding in use, and that makes it a locale-dependent operation.  It is not clear) 1463 SB
600 2355 1385 (to me how to propagate the information to the place where it is needed.  It) 1385 SB
600 2404 1478 (would like to avoid a \221virtual-function-call-per-character\222 when reading lines of) 1478 SB
600 2453 752 (text, because of performance problems.\224) 752 SB
300 2551 210 (Resolution:) 210 SB
600 2551 1087 (Resolved with the acceptance of N0611=95-0011 in Austin.) 1087 SB
300 2600 197 (Requester:) 197 SB
600 2600 715 (Beman Dawes: beman@dawes.win.net) 715 SB
